    "summary": "EODHD exposes a financial data REST API at `https://eodhd.com/api` authenticated by API key query parameter, plus two hosted MCP server endpoints: v1 with API-key auth and v2 with OAuth 2.1 discovery-based auth.",
    "description": "EODHD provides financial market data including historical and live prices, fundamentals, news, technical indicators, options, and macroeconomic datasets. The service is operated by Unicorn Data Services and is aimed at developers, traders, and AI-agent workflows.",
    "credentials": {
      "api_key": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "EODHD API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://eodhd.com/register",
        "setup": "Create an account at [EODHD registration](https://eodhd.com/register). After signup or subscribing to a plan, get your personal API key from your EODHD account/dashboard; EODHD's docs and `llms.txt` state this key is used on the REST API as the `api_token` query parameter, and the MCP v1 server accepts it as `apikey` in the URL. A limited demo value `demo` exists for a small set of symbols, but for real integrations use your own key from [register](https://eodhd.com/register)."
      },
      "mcp_oauth": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "EODHD MCP OAuth 2.1 authorization",
        "generateUrl": "https://mcp.eodhd.com/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server",
        "setup": "Use an MCP client that supports OAuth 2.1 with discovery, such as Claude Desktop. Connect to `https://mcp.eodhd.com/v2/mcp`; the client discovers the OAuth server from [authorization server metadata](https://mcp.eodhd.com/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server), performs PKCE, and can dynamically register a client at `https://mcp.eodhd.com/register`. EODHD's MCP docs describe v2 as OAuth 2.1 for Claude Desktop, with no API key in the URL."
      }
    },
